&nbsp;because&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:57px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">the&nbsp;results&nbsp;are&nbsp;averaged&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:76px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">over&nbsp;more&nbsp;experiments.&nbsp;The&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:95px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">split&nbsp;size&nbsp;also&nbsp;matters:&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:114px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">using&nbsp;more&nbsp;training&nbsp;data&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:133px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">usually&nbsp;improves&nbsp;accuracy,&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:152px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">while&nbsp;a&nbsp;larger&nbsp;validation&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:171px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">set&nbsp;may&nbsp;slightly&nbsp;reduce&nbsp;it&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:190px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">but&nbsp;gives&nbsp;a&nbsp;more&nbsp;reliable&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:209px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">estimate.&nbsp;Compared&nbsp;to&nbsp;1-NN,&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:228px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">the&nbsp;3-NN&nbsp;classifier&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:247px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">generally&nbsp;gives&nbsp;more&nbsp;stable&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:266px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">and&nbsp;slightly&nbsp;better&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:285px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">accuracy&nbsp;because&nbsp;it&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style="top:304px;height:19px;" class="view-line"><span><span class="mtk1">considers&nbsp;multiple&