        <div class="text-top-div">
          <div class="markdown"><span><p>When the number of splits increases, the accuracy becomes more stable because the results are averaged over more experiments. The split size also matters: using more training data usually improves accuracy, while a larger validation set may slightly reduce it but gives a more reliable estimate. Compared to 1-NN, the 3-NN classifier generally gives more stable and slightly better accuracy because it considers multiple neighbors instead of just one.</p>
</span></div>
